{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QzcgvSTdTKCoJzeMbicYef","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"pod-0 is PRIMARY. Now I need to create the admin user and app user. Since auth is enabled with `--auth`, I can create users on the PRIMARY before authentication is fully set up. \n\nWait, actually there's a subtle issue here. We started MongoDB with `--auth` flag AND `--keyFile`. When started with keyFile, MongoDB requires authentication even for local connections. However, there's a special case: when MongoDB is started with keyFile and there are no users at all yet, it allows a brief \"localhost exception\" that allows you to create the first user without authenticating.\n\nActually, with keyFile authentication, the localhost exception should still work for creating the very first admin user. \n\nLet me set up the admin user now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":311,"cache_read_input_tokens":35776,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":311},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f73f7be-48d7-42fd-9e86-8908e105392d","uuid":"db3d7ec0-9f62-4c44-8af6-9502a3d31887","request_id":"req_011CcQ6Aufvw7pqYMEJjAYFV"}
